                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d439">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">White</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Hay</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Embassy of the United States</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">London</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1902-12-20">
                            <hi rend="italic">December 20, 1902</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>(Mr. White reports that in accordance with the Department’s instruction he has
                    conveyed intimation in connection with suggestion as to arbitration at The
                    Hague, in the manner therein directed to the under secretary of state for
                    foreign affairs, who has telegraphed it to Lord Lansdowne. The latter will be
                    absent from London until Monday, when Mr. White will see him.)</p>
            </div>
        </body>
